          "Lifecycle of a team-up connection between two outward accounts (#501):\n  - `pending`: a team-up request was sent and is awaiting a response.\n  - `accepted`: both sides are connected and may message + collaborate.\n  - `declined`: the recipient declined the request.\n  - `removed`: a previously-accepted connection was removed by either side.\n`declined` and `removed` rows are reactivated as a fresh `pending`\nrequest when either side calls \/users\/{userId}\/connect again.\n",
